Babacan Says Economic Policy Aims for “Balanced” Consumption

-- B y   A l i   B e r a t   M e r i c
-- 
2011-10-13T06:34:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/babacan-says-economic-policy-aims-for-balanced-consumption.html
Turkey ’s revised medium-term
economic program will encourage “thrift” and aim for
“balanced consumption”, Deputy Prime Minister Ali Babacan
said.  Turkey’s savings rate fell to 12 percent while the
investment rate is at 21 percent, widening the current account
deficit along with energy imports, Babacan said in Ankara today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ali Berat Meric in Ankara at 
 americ@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
